item.title: How do u change the home start off spot (317) server can u help?
item.dc:creator: @P_I_M_P_3_D_Tut `Lewk_
item.description:
@P_I_M_P_3_D_Tut wrote:

[quote=“x blitz x, post:5, topic:257428”][quote author=P I M P 3 D Tut link=topic=339858.msg2634310#msg2634310 date=1232399319]

search in client.java for “home”
and then change the coordinates to urs.
[/quote] Listen. Not everyone’s client is going to have a “Home” command.
That’s like downloading a random file and searching
“OMG I CAN HAS SASQUATCH”.

if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("home")) { Home(); }

Public void Home () { sendMessage("ADD A MESSAGE HERE?"); // Optional. teleportToX = X; teleportToY = Y; }
Replace X & Y With your coords.

Home should be de-capitalized, Java coding conventions ;)[/quote] Ah, Thank you. Fixed.
